Start
/ F1 (load-bearing): a signed Data added to a list, persisted via the .plang wire
/ and read back, still verifies at %list[0]%. The wire self-describes each element
/ as Data so the signature survives at rest inside the collection.
- sign "hello world", write to %signed%
- add %signed% to %list%
- save %list% to file 'signed_list_roundtrip.plang'
- read file 'signed_list_roundtrip.plang', write to %roundtrip%
- verify %roundtrip[0]%, write to %ok%
- assert %ok% equals true
- delete file 'signed_list_roundtrip.plang'
